{"title_page": "WRQK-FM", "text_new": "{{short description|Active rock radio station in Canton, Ohio}}\n{{third-party|date=July 2017}}\n{{Infobox radio station\n|name               = WRQK-FM\n|image              = WRQK-FM logo.png\n|city               = [[Canton, Ohio|Canton]], [[Ohio]]\n|area               = [[Canton\u2013Massillon, Ohio metropolitan area|Canton]]-[[Akron metropolitan area|Akron]] metro areas\n|branding           = '''Rock 106.9'''\n|slogan             = Canton's Rock Station \n|frequency          = 106.9 [[Hertz|MHz]] {{HD Radio}}\n|airdate            = March 1, 1961\n|format             = [[Mainstream rock]]<br>HD2: [[Sports radio]]\n|erp                = 27,500 [[watt]]s\n|haat               = 103 meters\n|class              = B\n|facility_id        = 8550\n|coordinates        = {{nowrap|{{coord|40|49|22.00|N|81|25|40.00|W|region:US-OH_type:landmark_source:FCC}}}}\n|callsign_meaning   = '''<u>RQK</u>''' resembles \"[[Rock music|Rock]]\"\n|former_callsigns   = WCNO (1961&ndash;67)<br>WNYN-FM (1967&ndash;71)<br>WHLQ (1971&ndash;79)<br>WOOS-FM (1979&ndash;85)<br>WRQK (1985&ndash;89)\n|affiliations       = [[iHeartRadio]]<br>[[Premiere Networks]]<br>[[List of programming syndicated by Clear Channel#Premium Choice|Premium Choice]]<br>[[United Stations Radio Networks]]\n|owner              = [[iHeartMedia, Inc.]]\n|licensee           = Capstar TX LLC\n|sister_stations    = [[WHLO]], [[WHOF]], [[WKDD]]\n|webcast            = [http://www.iheart.com/live/3294/?autoplay=true Listen Live]\n|website            = {{URL|wrqk.com}}\n}}\n\n'''WRQK-FM''' (106.9 [[FM broadcasting|FM]]) &ndash; branded '''Rock 106.9''' &ndash; is a commercial [[mainstream rock]] [[Radio broadcasting|radio station]] licensed to [[Canton, Ohio|Canton]], [[Ohio]], serving both the [[Canton\u2013Massillon, Ohio metropolitan area|Canton]] and [[Akron metropolitan area|Akron]] metro areas.  Owned by [[iHeartMedia, Inc.]], the station serves as the local affiliate for ''[[Nikki Sixx#Radio shows|Sixx Sense with Nikki Sixx]]'', and ''[[The House of Hair with Dee Snider]]''.  The WRQK-FM studios are located in [[North Canton, Ohio|North Canton]], while the station transmitter resides in Canton.  In addition to a standard [[analog transmission]], WRQK-FM broadcasts over two [[HD Radio]] channels, and is available online via [[iHeartRadio]].\n\n==History==\nWRQK-FM began broadcasting as '''WCNO''' on March 1, 1961.<ref>http://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-BC-YB-IDX/60s-OCR-YB/1965-YB/1965-BC-YB-for-OCR-Page-0280.pdf</ref>  The new station was owned by the Greer Group, also owner of [[WCER (AM)|WAND]]-[[Canton, Ohio|Canton]]; the two stations became WNYN and '''WNYN-FM''' in 1967.  Both stations were purchased in 1965 by Don Keyes, who had made his mark as a national programmer for legendary station owner [[Gordon McLendon]]. In 1971, he sold the FM station to [[Susquehanna Radio Corporation]], the owners of [[WHLO]] (AM) Akron, and it became '''WHLQ'''.\n\nSusquehanna sold the station in 1978 to the owners of WINW, who applied to change the FM call letters to WHOF (for the \"Hall of Fame\" city of Canton) but were rebuffed by the owners of WTOF, another local FM station. (Coincidentally, WRQK-FM now has a new Clear Channel sister station using the [[WHOF]] call letters.) 106.9 adopted an automated Top 40 format and became '''WOOS-FM''' on June 1, 1979.\n\nWOOS-FM changed its call sign to '''WRQK''' on August 3, 1985, taking on an [[album oriented rock]] music format.  For a while, the station called itself '''Goodrock 107''', an apparent play on the name of the [[Goodyear Tire and Rubber Company]] in nearby [[Akron, Ohio|Akron]]. It formally changed from WRQK to '''WRQK-FM''' on February 14, 1989, when AM station [[WINW]] changed its call sign to WRQK. The AM station changed back to WINW six months later, but the FM call sign has remained WRQK-FM.\n\nIn 1995, the station was sold by Jim Embrescia's Canton/Akron Radio, Inc. to Sabre Communications. Then In 1997, SabreComm sold to Connoisseur.  Connoisseur sold their entire radio group to [[Cumulus]]. Then, on August 8, 2006, it was announced that WRQK-FM would be sold to [[Clear Channel Communications]], pairing WRQK-FM with former partner [[WHLO]], as well as [[WARF]], [[WKDD]], and [[WHOF]]. Clear Channel took over operations of WRQK-FM on January 15, 2007, pending FCC approval of its purchase of the station from Cumulus.\n\nIn March 2007, WRQK-FM changed its branding from '''Rock&nbsp;107''' to '''Rock&nbsp;106.9'''. It also changed its slogan from \"Canton's Rock Station\" to \"It Just Rocks!\", in an effort to also serve the Akron market, in early 2017 the station changed the slogan back to \"Canton's Rock Station\"\n\n==Current programming==\nWRQK-FM personality and former ''[[Maxwell Show]]'' sidekick Dan Stansbury hosts the morning drive program.<ref>[http://www.wrqk.com/onair/the-stansbury-show-54609/ Stansbury on WRQK - WRQK.com]</ref> Local DJ \"Captain\" Tony McGinty is heard in afternoon drive,<ref>[http://www.wrqk.com/onair/captain-tony-53761/ Captain Tony on WRQK - WRQK.com]</ref> and other music programming is provided via the [[List of programming syndicated by Clear Channel#Premium Choice|Premium Choice]] network.  WRQK-FM also airs ''[[Nikki Sixx#Radio shows|Sixx Sense with Nikki Sixx]]'' weekday evenings,  via [[Premiere Networks]]; and ''[[The House of Hair with Dee Snider]]'' on weekends via [[United Stations Radio Networks]].  The HD2 [[digital subchannel]] carries the [[sports radio]] format of [[Fox Sports Radio]].<ref>[http://www.sixxsense.com/pages/radiostations.html?state=ohio Sixx Sense stations - Sixx Sense.com]</ref><ref>[http://houseofhaironline.com/house-of-hair-stations-list-by-state/ House of Hair Stations - House of Hair online.com]</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|http://www.wrqk.com}}\n*{{FM station data|WRQK}}\n\n{{Canton Radio}}\n{{Active Rock Radio Stations in Ohio}}\n{{Clear Channel}}\n\n[[Category:1961 establishments in Ohio]]\n[[Category:Active rock radio stations in the United States]]\n[[Category:Radio stations established in 1961]]\n[[Category:Radio stations in Ohio|RQK-FM]]\n[[Category:IHeartMedia radio stations]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Active rock radio station in Canton, Ohio}}\n{{third-party|date=July 2017}}\n{{Infobox radio station\n|name               = WRQK-FM\n|image              = WRQK-FM logo.png\n|city               = [[Canton, Ohio|Canton]], [[Ohio]]\n|area               = [[Canton\u2013Massillon, Ohio metropolitan area|Canton]]-[[Akron metropolitan area|Akron]] metro areas\n|branding           = '''Rock 106.9'''\n|slogan             = Canton's Rock Station \n|frequency          = 106.9 [[Hertz|MHz]] {{HD Radio}}\n|airdate            = March 1, 1961\n|format             = [[Mainstream rock]]<br>HD2: [[Sports radio]]\n|erp                = 27,500 [[watt]]s\n|haat               = 103 meters\n|class              = B\n|facility_id        = 8550\n|coordinates        = {{nowrap|{{coord|40|49|22.00|N|81|25|40.00|W|region:US-OH_type:landmark_source:FCC}}}}\n|callsign_meaning   = '''<u>RQK</u>''' resembles \"[[Rock music|Rock]]\"\n|former_callsigns   = WCNO (1961&ndash;67)<br>WNYN-FM (1967&ndash;71)<br>WHLQ (1971&ndash;79)<br>WOOS-FM (1979&ndash;85)<br>WRQK (1985&ndash;89)\n|affiliations       = [[iHeartRadio]]<br>[[Premiere Networks]]<br>[[List of programming syndicated by Clear Channel#Premium Choice|Premium Choice]]<br>[[United Stations Radio Networks]]\n|owner              = [[iHeartMedia, Inc.]]\n|licensee           = Capstar TX LLC\n|sister_stations    = [[WHLO]], [[WHOF]], [[WKDD]]\n|webcast            = [http://www.iheart.com/live/3294/?autoplay=true Listen Live]\n|website            = {{URL|wrqk.com}}\n}}\n\n'''WRQK-FM''' (106.9 [[FM broadcasting|FM]]) &ndash; branded '''Rock 106.9''' &ndash; is a commercial [[mainstream rock]] [[Radio broadcasting|radio station]] licensed to [[Canton, Ohio|Canton]], [[Ohio]], serving both the [[Canton\u2013Massillon, Ohio metropolitan area|Canton]] and [[Akron metropolitan area|Akron]] metro areas.  Owned by [[iHeartMedia, Inc.]], the station serves as the local affiliate for ''[[Nikki Sixx#Radio shows|Sixx Sense with Nikki Sixx]]'', and ''[[The House of Hair with Dee Snider]]''.  The WRQK-FM studios are located in [[North Canton, Ohio|North Canton]], while the station transmitter resides in Canton.  In addition to a standard [[analog transmission]], WRQK-FM broadcasts over two [[HD Radio]] channels, and is available online via [[iHeartRadio]].\n\n==History==\nWRQK-FM began broadcasting as '''WCNO''' on March 1, 1961.<ref>http://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-BC-YB-IDX/60s-OCR-YB/1965-YB/1965-BC-YB-for-OCR-Page-0280.pdf</ref>  The new station was owned by the Greer Group, also owner of [[WCER (AM)|WAND]]/[[Canton, Ohio|Canton]]; the two stations became WNYN and '''WNYN-FM''' in 1967.  Both stations were purchased in 1965 by Don Keyes, who had made his mark as a national programmer for legendary station owner [[Gordon McLendon]]. In 1971, he sold the FM station to [[Susquehanna Radio Corporation]], the owners of [[WHLO]] (AM) Akron, and it became '''WHLQ'''.\n\nSusquehanna sold the station in 1978 to the owners of WINW, who applied to change the FM call letters to WHOF (for the \"Hall of Fame\" city of Canton) but were rebuffed by the owners of WTOF, another local FM station. (Coincidentally, WRQK-FM now has a new Clear Channel sister station using the [[WHOF]] call letters.) 106.9 adopted an automated Top 40 format and became '''WOOS-FM''' on June 1, 1979.\n\nWOOS-FM changed its call sign to '''WRQK''' on August 3, 1985, taking on an [[album oriented rock]] music format.  For a while, the station called itself '''Goodrock 107''', an apparent play on the name of the [[Goodyear Tire and Rubber Company]] in nearby [[Akron, Ohio|Akron]]. It formally changed from WRQK to '''WRQK-FM''' on February 14, 1989, when AM station [[WINW]] changed its call sign to WRQK. The AM station changed back to WINW six months later, but the FM call sign has remained WRQK-FM.\n\nIn 1995, the station was sold by Jim Embrescia's Canton/Akron Radio, Inc. to Sabre Communications. Then In 1997, SabreComm sold to Connoisseur.  Connoisseur sold their entire radio group to [[Cumulus]]. Then, on August 8, 2006, it was announced that WRQK-FM would be sold to [[Clear Channel Communications]], pairing WRQK-FM with former partner [[WHLO]], as well as [[WARF]], [[WKDD]], and [[WHOF]]. Clear Channel took over operations of WRQK-FM on January 15, 2007, pending FCC approval of its purchase of the station from Cumulus.\n\nIn March 2007, WRQK-FM changed its branding from '''Rock&nbsp;107''' to '''Rock&nbsp;106.9'''. It also changed its slogan from \"Canton's Rock Station\" to \"It Just Rocks!\", in an effort to also serve the Akron market, in early 2017 the station changed the slogan back to \"Canton's Rock Station\"\n\n==Current programming==\nWRQK-FM personality and former ''[[Maxwell Show]]'' sidekick Dan Stansbury hosts the morning drive program.<ref>[http://www.wrqk.com/onair/the-stansbury-show-54609/ Stansbury on WRQK - WRQK.com]</ref> Local DJ \"Captain\" Tony McGinty is heard in afternoon drive,<ref>[http://www.wrqk.com/onair/captain-tony-53761/ Captain Tony on WRQK - WRQK.com]</ref> and other music programming is provided via the [[List of programming syndicated by Clear Channel#Premium Choice|Premium Choice]] network.  WRQK-FM also airs ''[[Nikki Sixx#Radio shows|Sixx Sense with Nikki Sixx]]'' weekday evenings,  via [[Premiere Networks]]; and ''[[The House of Hair with Dee Snider]]'' on weekends via [[United Stations Radio Networks]].  The HD2 [[digital subchannel]] carries the [[sports radio]] format of [[Fox Sports Radio]].<ref>[http://www.sixxsense.com/pages/radiostations.html?state=ohio Sixx Sense stations - Sixx Sense.com]</ref><ref>[http://houseofhaironline.com/house-of-hair-stations-list-by-state/ House of Hair Stations - House of Hair online.com]</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|http://www.wrqk.com}}\n*{{FM station data|WRQK}}\n\n{{Canton Radio}}\n{{Active Rock Radio Stations in Ohio}}\n{{Clear Channel}}\n\n[[Category:1961 establishments in Ohio]]\n[[Category:Active rock radio stations in the United States]]\n[[Category:Radio stations established in 1961]]\n[[Category:Radio stations in Ohio|RQK-FM]]\n[[Category:IHeartMedia radio stations]]\n", "name_user": "Stereorock", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eHistory", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WRQK-FM"}
